1. You want to add a comment to your style sheet that says “temporary.” Which is the proper line to add to the CSS file?
A. //temporary
B. --temporary
C. /* temporary */ X
D. rem temporary

2. You want to maintain separation between structure and presentation. How do you create your style rules?
A. Use inline styles.
B. Use embedded styles.
C. Use external style sheets. X
D. In the HTML document, specify @import to load style sheets.

3. You want your printer.css style sheet to target printers. How would you set up the style sheet link?
A. <link rel=’printer’ type=’text/css’ href=’Content/printer.css’ />
B. <link rel=’stylesheet’ type=’text/css’ href=’Content/printer.css’ media=’print’ /> X
C. <link rel=’stylesheet’ type=’text/css’ href=’Content/printer.css’ />
D. <link rel=’stylesheet’ type=’text/css’ href=’Content/printer.css’ target=’print’ />